omx

Class OmxMatrix<D,C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • omx.AttributedElement
      • omx.OmxMatrix<D,C>
  • Type Parameters:
    D - The type of the data container the matrix uses. This will always be a two-dimensional array of some sort.
    C - The object-equivalent type of the component (base) type of <D>.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OmxMatrix.OmxByteMatrix, OmxMatrix.OmxDoubleMatrix, OmxMatrix.OmxFloatMatrix, OmxMatrix.OmxIntMatrix, OmxMatrix.OmxShortMatrix, OmxMatrix.OmxStringMatrix

    public class OmxMatrix<D,C>
extends AttributedElement
    The OmxMatrix class provides access to OMX matrix data. OMX matrix data is two-dimensional, rectangular data of a basic type (numeric or text) with an optionally specified missing value identifier. In addition to the matrix data itself, this container provides information on the shape of the matrix, its name, and other metadata.

    This class is parameterized by the type of its data container (<D>) and the type of its values's (Java) equivalent object (<C>). Only a limited set of <D,C> pairs are allowed, and are as follows:

    Data container (D) Data object equivalent (C)
    byte[][] Byte
    short[][] Short
    int[][] Integer
    float[][] Float
    double[][] Double
    String[][] String

    Because of this restriction, instances of this classes will generally not be (directly) needed. Instead, one of the subclasses created from the static Omx[DATATYPE]Matrix classes provided in this class should be used.

    Note that instances of this class intentionally do not provide full immutability guarantees. First, the missing value identifier (which indicates the matrix value that should represent a "missing" value) may be changed/set after construction. Additionally, while the data container may not be changed, its values are allowed to be modified; the OmxMatrix instance will detect any changes and write them to the OMX file if a save is requested. For large matrices, this avoids the need to copy large (internal) data arrays when modifying data in-place.

         D data,

        Constructor specifying the name, data, and missing value for the matrix.
        Parameters:
        name - The matrix name.
        data - The matrix data. This should be a rectangular (not jagged) array.
        missingValue - The value to use for missing values in the matrix.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if data is not a two-dimensional array or is empty; or if the component class of data is not one of the allowed types or does not match the object-equivalent class of missingValue.

      • transfer

        public void transfer(omx.hdf5.OmxMutableDataset dataset)
        Transfer the data held in this matrix to an OMX dataset. This functionality is mainly intended for users interacting with the HDF5 OMX data structures directly, and should not be needed for general use. Note that this copies not only the data, but also metadata (attributes and the value used for missing values).
        Parameters:
        dataset - The dataset to transfer the data to.

      • getMatrix

        public static OmxMatrix getMatrix(omx.hdf5.OmxDataset dataset)
        Get an OmxMatrix corresponding to an OMX dataset. The returned matrix will have an implicit connection to the source dataset, which can be useful when modifying and/or saving data. Note that this method will fail if the dataset holds an unallowed type or is not two-dimensional.
        Parameters:
        dataset - The dataset that the matrix will be built from.
        Returns:
        a matrix representing dataset.
